Grammar

    0 $accept: config $end

    1 config: %empty
    2       | config assignment

    3 assignment: SET IDENTIFIER EQUALS VALUE SEMICOLON


Terminals, with rules where they appear

    $end (0) 0
    error (256)
    SET (258) 3
    EQUALS (259) 3
    SEMICOLON (260) 3
    VALUE <ival> (261) 3
    IDENTIFIER <sval> (262) 3


Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

    $accept (8)
        on left: 0
    config (9)
        on left: 1 2
        on right: 0 2
    assignment (10)
        on left: 3
        on right: 2


State 0

    0 $accept: . config $end

    $default  reduce using rule 1 (config)

    config  go to state 1


State 1

    0 $accept: config . $end
    2 config: config . assignment

    $end  shift, and go to state 2
    SET   shift, and go to state 3

    assignment  go to state 4


State 2

    0 $accept: config $end .

    $default  accept


State 3

    3 assignment: SET . IDENTIFIER EQUALS VALUE SEMICOLON

    IDENTIFIER  shift, and go to state 5


State 4

    2 config: config assignment .

    $default  reduce using rule 2 (config)


State 5

    3 assignment: SET IDENTIFIER . EQUALS VALUE SEMICOLON

    EQUALS  shift, and go to state 6


State 6

    3 assignment: SET IDENTIFIER EQUALS . VALUE SEMICOLON

    VALUE  shift, and go to state 7


State 7

    3 assignment: SET IDENTIFIER EQUALS VALUE . SEMICOLON

    SEMICOLON  shift, and go to state 8


State 8

    3 assignment: SET IDENTIFIER EQUALS VALUE SEMICOLON .

    $default  reduce using rule 3 (assignment)
